<li id="cite_note-110"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-110">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Page, Clarence (5 December 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-12-05/news/ct-oped-1205-page-20121205_1_homophobia-islamophobia-fear">"Words with negative power"</a>. <i>Chicago Tribune</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">16 December</span> 2012</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomophobia&amp;rft.atitle=Words+with+negative+power&amp;rft.aufirst=Clarence&amp;rft.aulast=Page&amp;rft.au=Page%2C+Clarence&amp;rft.date=5+December+2012&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farticles.chicagotribune.com%2F2012-12-05%2Fnews%2Fct-oped-1205-page-20121205_1_homophobia-islamophobia-fear&amp;rft.jtitle=Chicago+Tribune&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-111"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-111">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Michelson, Noah (5 December 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/12/05/associated-press-ban-homophobia-discussion_n_2245697.html">"Huffington Post discussion"</a>. <i>Huffington Post</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">16 December</span> 2012</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomophobia&amp;rft.atitle=Huffington+Post+discussion&amp;rft.aufirst=Noah&amp;rft.aulast=Michelson&amp;rft.au=Michelson%2C+Noah&amp;rft.date=5+December+2012&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.com%2F2012%2F12%2F05%2Fassociated-press-ban-homophobia-discussion_n_2245697.html&amp;rft.jtitle=Huffington+Post&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-latimes-112"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-latimes_112-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Rainey, James (28 November 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.latimes.com/news/politics/la-pn-ap-homophobia-style-book-20121128,0,2905541.story">"No more 'homophobia'? AP raises the question"</a>. <i>Los Angeles Times</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">16 December</span> 2012</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomophobia&amp;rft.atitle=No+more+%27homophobia%27%3F+AP+raises+the+question&amp;rft.aufirst=James&amp;rft.aulast=Rainey&amp;rft.au=Rainey%2C+James&amp;rft.date=28+November+2012&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fla-pn-ap-homophobia-style-book-20121128%2C0%2C2905541.story&amp;rft.jtitle=Los+Angeles+Times&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> <a href="/wiki/Baltimore_Sun" title="Baltimore Sun" class="mw-redirect">Baltimore Sun</a> language authority John McIntyre described it as "reasoned, principled, and wrong-headed," while National Lesbian and Gay Journalists Association President Michael Triplett advocates terms such as "LGBT rights opponents"</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-113"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-113">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Frank, Nathaniel (27 November 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.slate.com/articles/double_x/doublex/2012/11/the_ap_bans_homophobia_is_the_word_really_inaccurate.html">"The Associated Press Bans Homophobia"</a>. <i>Slate</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">16 December</span> 2012</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomophobia&amp;rft.atitle=The+Associated+Press+Bans+Homophobia&amp;rft.aufirst=Nathaniel&amp;rft.au=Frank%2C+Nathaniel&amp;rft.aulast=Frank&amp;rft.date=27+November+2012&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.slate.com%2Farticles%2Fdouble_x%2Fdoublex%2F2012%2F11%2Fthe_ap_bans_homophobia_is_the_word_really_inaccurate.html&amp;rft.jtitle=Slate&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> Nathaniel Frank of <a href="/wiki/Slate_(magazine)" title="Slate (magazine)">Slate</a> suggested that "In pursuit of accuracy, the standard-setters (got) it wrong" and that Minthorn's words were "oddly amorphous phrases for a standards editor".</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-noonan1999-114"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-noonan1999_114-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-noonan1999_114-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-noonan1999_114-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web">Raymond J. Noonan (November 6, 1999). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://home.bway.net/rjnoonan/Conf1999.html">"Heterophobia: The Evolution of an Idea"</a>. Dr. Ray Noonan’s 1999 Conference Presentations<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">November 25,</span> 2012</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomophobia&amp;rft.aulast=Raymond+J.+Noonan&amp;rft.au=Raymond+J.+Noonan&amp;rft.btitle=Heterophobia%3A+The+Evolution+of+an+Idea&amp;rft.date=November+6%2C+1999&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fhome.bway.net%2Frjnoonan%2FConf1999.html&amp;rft.pub=Dr.+Ray+Noonan%E2%80%99s+1999+Conference+Presentations&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-115"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-115">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Kinsey, Sex and Fraud: The Indoctrination of a People. An Investigation Into the Human Sexuality Research of Alfred C. Kinsey, Wardell B. Pomeroy, Clyde E. Martin, and Paul H. Gebhard</i> by Judith A. Reisman and Edward W. Eichel</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-116"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-116">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>The Complete Dictionary of Sexuality</i> by Robert T. Francoeur</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Franzini-117"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Franzini_117-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal">White, Stephen M. and Franzini, Louis R. (1999). "Heteronegativism? The attitudes of gay men and lesbians toward heterosexuals. Journal of Homosexuality". <i>Journal of Homosexuality</i> <b>37</b> (1): 65–79. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//dx.doi.org/10.1300%2Fj082v37n01_05">10.1300/j082v37n01_05</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomophobia&amp;rft.atitle=Heteronegativism%3F+The+attitudes+of+gay+men+and+lesbians+toward+heterosexuals.+Journal+of+Homosexuality&amp;rft.aulast=White%2C+Stephen+M.+and+Franzini%2C+Louis+R.&amp;rft.au=White%2C+Stephen+M.+and+Franzini%2C+Louis+R.&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1300%2Fj082v37n01_05&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Homosexuality&amp;rft.pages=65-79&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=37" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
